description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job title: &lt;/strong&gt;Audiology Assistant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;£21,000 – £24,000 depending on experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Southampton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;36 hours per week, Monday to Sunday rota&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opening for an &lt;strong&gt;Audiology Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team in &lt;strong&gt;Southampton&lt;/strong&gt;. This role is full time working 36 hours per week across a rota from &lt;strong&gt;Monday to Sunday&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Audiology Assistant you will help to ensure the smooth running of the working day by undertaking and assisting with audiology procedures, ensuring that effective and efficient patient care is always delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you be responsible for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertaking and assisting with audiology procedures in line with best practice technique&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing support to ensure the appropriate examination of patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that clinically validated appointments are booked efficiently and accurately on the internal system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing the patient’s pre-procedure data protection form/consent form (where applicable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing and monitoring patients’ condition after their procedure, ensuring any changes are reported to the relevant staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing administrative tasks within the department and providing clinical and clerical support to the practitioners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In order to apply, you should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of using audiological equipment in a healthcare setting  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A demonstratable appreciation of patient care and confidentiality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work independently and as part of a multi skilled team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong listening skills with an ability to present information in a logical manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent administrative skills and an ability to pick new systems up quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can InHealth offer you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a highly competitive salary and a generous flexible benefits package, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days holiday plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private medical insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plus access to various discounts!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you the opportunity to do something you love, with the right support to access the roles you want, through clear career paths and best-in-class training and development.  This is an environment where you have accountability for your career and can make a real contribution to the organization and to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;InHealth is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all areas of the community.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
